parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear backup camera can cause safety risks, especially when reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear backup camera display is blank
or not functioning; the camera is not detected; or the camera is stuck on a static image.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated/ventilated seat electrical system can cause a fire hazard, especially if the connector under the passenger seat is burnt.
symptoms: The heated/ventilated seats stop working; a burning smell is present; or the connector under the passenger seat is burnt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to safety risks, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls; no warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause safety risks, especially if it leads to a fire or loss of critical vehicle functions.
symptoms: A burning smell is present; the electrical system malfunctions; or the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 3rd brake light harness can cause safety risks, especially if it leads to a failure of the brake light system.
symptoms: The 3rd brake light does not function; the harness is damaged or corroded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the evaporator core can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to poor air quality, discomfort, and potential health risks due to refrigerant leaks.

the air conditioning system is not cooling properly
and visibility issues due to windshield residue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door system can cause the doors to open while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

the doors do not close properly
and warning lights or alerts indicating door malfunctions.
